2022 was a big year for me, filled with adventures, laughter, tears, strength, and most importantly, love. 
In lots of ways, this post is a love letter to my person, my twin flame, my Michael. 

This year, I lost my 18 year old cat, my best buddy, Magic. He was my whole world, and if I hadn’t simultaneously met Michael just one month before, I don’t think I could have survived that loss. So to my love for being one of the only people Magic ever liked, for driving us to vet appointments, and for holding my baby and I after he took his last breath, I will be forever grateful. In the midst of my darkest hour, you were the brightest light I could have hoped for. 

We had a lot of highs and lows this year, and in the worst of those times I still believed in us, in you. I prayed not only for your well-being, but that God would help us find our way back to each other. Though it was a long and winding road, here we are: Together and so much stronger now than we were before! 

I am so proud of you for how far you’ve come, and for the amazing man that you are. You are the strongest person I know, Michael Lawrence, and I love you more every day. I am so lucky you’re my guy! 

Here’s to us, our future, and to the joy I hope lies ahead in 2023! Happy New Year, everyone ❤️.
.
.

It has been one year without you, my Magic. How can time move so quickly and so slowly, all at once? 
I remember the slow beat of your heart that day, your little breaths, the way you looked at me and I couldn’t imagine life without my baby, my soulmate. 
I whispered to you how you were, and still are, my world. My everything. My very best friend. I thanked you for always loving me, for being my best boy. My wittle.
It was the most impossible goodbye, the hardest see you later I have ever had to say. 
I feel your spirit with me every day, my sweet bun. I am so blessed to have had the most wonderful cat, the handsomest boy in all the lands. There will never be a day when I don’t miss and love you with every ounce of my being.
I can’t wait to see you again, happy and healthy. I hope I brought you as much joy as you brought me.
I love you Magic.
